2vPKjFYIJyE.keywords: DJI Phantom Futaba UAV Maximo Park RC Flight DJI Phantom FPV DJI Phantom Carbon Fiber Props UAV RC Flight Cyclops Breeze OSD v1.0 DJI Phantom 8FG Super Quadcopter DJI Phantom Quadcopter Quadcopter Bridge Carbon Fiber Props Breeze OSD Air St Petersburg GoPro HD 3 Black Edition GoPro HD 3 Black Gulf of MexicoDJI Phantom FPV with Carbon Fiber Props 6213High Altitude Tests My first flight with the carbon fiber propellers. I was using a combination of line of sight and a 10" portable LCD. I managed to get up to 400 feet at 310, and the view was spectacular! The updown that you see in the video was me testing the gimbal's axis. Filmed at Maximo Park St. Petersburg, FL Pros Lot's of power and speed They won't break or snap off during hard flying Sound and look great! Cons Setting the gains is tricky...it's hard to get rid of the wobble The Phantom seems to drift a lot more Must use strong threadlock liquid if you want to keep the default prop nuts VERY DANGEROUS! The Phantom ends up becoming a flying chainsaw! Verdict I think I'll stick with the DJI black props...don't get me wrong, the carbon fiber ones are slick, but I don't like the tradeoffs unless I can perfect the gains to be a lot more stable.
